    rationale: "Methotrexate is a folate antagonist used for psoriasis, rheumatoid arthritis, and malignancy. Its primary toxicities include bone marrow suppression (causing thrombocytopenia, leukopenia, anemia \u2014 all relevant to surgical bleeding risk and infection) and hepatotoxicity (causing fibrosis and cirrhosis with chronic use \u2014 relevant to drug metabolism and coagulopathy). A CBC assesses hematologic toxicity and a liver function panel assesses hepatic toxicity. While methotrexate is renally cleared and renal function is important, creatinine alone is insufficient. Methotrexate does not cause hyperkalemia. Psoriasis itself is associated with mild cardiovascular risk but not a primary hypercoagulable state.",
