    rationale: "Pressure injuries at bony prominences (greater trochanter, sacrum, heels, occiput) are a known perioperative risk, particularly in prolonged procedures. Preoperative skin assessment should identify high-risk areas \u2014 thin skin, existing erythema, bony prominences with minimal soft tissue coverage \u2014 and inform padding selection and positioning strategy. Failure to map these areas and plan appropriate pressure redistribution before positioning is the primary preventable failure. ECG, antibiotics, and coagulation assessment are important for other reasons but do not directly prevent pressure injuries from inadequate padding.",
