    rationale: "The ability to detect change over time \u2014 the 'E' (Evolution) in ABCDE \u2014 depends entirely on having an objective baseline. Precise measurement (6 mm \u2192 9 mm) and color description (dark brown \u2192 new black area) at the initial visit created a reproducible baseline that made the change detectable at follow-up. This is the clinical value of systematic, objective lesion documentation. Subjective patient complaints are unreliable for detecting subtle morphologic change. Photography is a useful adjunct but was not described as part of the documentation in this scenario. ABCDE criteria were applied at both visits, but the ability to detect evolution required the objective baseline documentation.",
