    rationale: "Normal epidermal cell turnover takes approximately one month, but this assumes adequate nutrition and immune function. Malnutrition deprives keratinocytes of the amino acids, vitamins (especially C and A), and zinc required for proliferation and collagen synthesis. Immunosuppression impairs the macrophage-mediated debridement and growth factor signaling that initiate the proliferative phase. Together, these factors significantly extend the healing timeline and increase infection risk. Wound depth alone does not determine healing time when systemic factors are impaired. Normal immune function facilitates, rather than impedes, wound healing. Reducing inflammation does not accelerate healing \u2014 the inflammatory phase is necessary for wound repair.",
